          <name>RENDER_SCALE</name>
          <briefdescription>
<para>The render scale of the text. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;renderScale&quot;, type Property::FLOAT. Renders text by rasterizing glyphs at a larger scale and downscaling the result. This improves rendering quality when the view is visually scaled, by reducing quality loss caused by texture upscaling. The layout size of the view is not affected. Valid only when async rendering is enabled, and the value must be 1.0f or greater. <simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classDali_1_1Ui_1_1Label_1ad535988007bd16b6b4b2009a1547d83f" kindref="member">Label::SetRenderScale()</ref>, <ref refid="classDali_1_1Ui_1_1Label_1ab37ce12482f7bc42fc5d830b10e6f846" kindref="member">Label::GetRenderScale()</ref>. </para>
